726581f-a.folder: Flushing Avenue & Seneca Avenue, Queens, NY
726581f-a.text:
1410 Flushing Avenue, at the S. E. corner of Seneca Avenue, showing the Covert-Jenkins Farmhouse and barns, viewing northeastward across cultivated land on Seneca Avenue. In the center background of the view is the Nicholas Wyckoff House, on the north side of Flushing Avenue. For additional data see the "New York
Sun," February 18, 1939.
View 1: 1922
View 2: 1923
Views 3,4: 1929
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

726583f-a.folder: Flushing Avenue & Seneca Avenue, Queens, NY
726583f-a.text:
1416 Flushing Ave., east side, north of Seneca Ave., showing the Onderdonck-Schoomaker house. Mrs. Ann Onderdonck and her heirs were owners from 1852-1884. This is a set of four views.. In 1767 Moses Biegel was the owner. For more data see the N.Y. Sun, February 18, 1939.

1922.

Views 1 and 4.
View 2: April 1929.
View 3: September 1928

Eugene L. Armbruster.
